WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:06.400
And last week we started a little mini series here on Wednesday evening as we get into the

00:00:06.400 --> 00:00:09.199
new year 2026.

00:00:09.199 --> 00:00:14.359
And someone reminded me today that we're almost halfway through the first month of the year.

00:00:14.359 --> 00:00:16.680
And I said, slow down, you know, slow down.

00:00:16.680 --> 00:00:17.680
And it's true.

00:00:17.680 --> 00:00:18.680
Tomorrow's the 15th.

00:00:18.680 --> 00:00:22.360
It's really amazing how quickly time flies.

00:00:22.360 --> 00:00:27.760
But last week we looked at just a single verse, Psalm 119, 126, it is time for the Lord to

00:00:27.760 --> 00:00:30.399
work for they have made void thy law.

00:00:30.399 --> 00:00:34.520
And I preached a message that I titled a longing to see God work.

00:00:34.520 --> 00:00:40.880
And as we examined that, that portion of scripture and made some points about it, we were encouraged

00:00:40.880 --> 00:00:43.119
to examine our own lives.

00:00:43.119 --> 00:00:47.200
And really, as we examine our own lives, we enter into this new year.

00:00:47.200 --> 00:00:51.159
The question is this, are we longing to see God work?

00:00:51.159 --> 00:00:57.119
Do we have that desire to see God do what only God can do?

00:00:57.479 --> 00:01:01.599
Do we recognize the ability that God has to work?

00:01:01.599 --> 00:01:06.879
The fact that he has all power, he is limitless, and he can do all things.

00:01:06.879 --> 00:01:11.480
He can just, he delights in answering prayer.

00:01:11.480 --> 00:01:14.839
And do we believe that God is able to work?

00:01:14.839 --> 00:01:18.919
And then we ask this question, do we recognize the need for God to work?

00:01:18.919 --> 00:01:21.599
We mentioned that the psalmist said they've made void thy law.

00:01:21.760 --> 00:01:27.319
And of course, we see, even in our own community and our own society, how they have disregarded

00:01:27.319 --> 00:01:29.120
the law of the Lord.

00:01:29.120 --> 00:01:33.279
And God's word is true, it's faithful, it's settled in heaven forever.

00:01:33.279 --> 00:01:38.720
And I am thankful that we have the Bible, but we understand that we need God to work.

00:01:38.720 --> 00:01:45.199
I ask this, we should have the desire that God would work in our lives individually.

00:01:45.199 --> 00:01:47.239
If you're married, that he'd work in your marriage.

00:01:47.239 --> 00:01:49.919
If you have a family, that he'd work in your home.

00:01:49.919 --> 00:01:56.120
That God would work in our church, in our community, in our commonwealth, in our nation,

00:01:56.120 --> 00:01:57.120
and in our world.

00:01:57.120 --> 00:02:01.239
And we really want to see God do what only God can do.

00:02:01.239 --> 00:02:03.199
And we took time to examine that.

00:02:03.199 --> 00:02:07.000
This evening, we're going to look at a portion of scripture in 2 Kings chapter number three.

00:02:07.000 --> 00:02:12.320
And as we examine this portion of scripture, we're going to note an event that took place

00:02:12.320 --> 00:02:13.839
in Israel's history.

00:02:13.839 --> 00:02:17.559
And really, we see Israel-Judah all together here.

00:02:17.559 --> 00:02:22.160
It's not a united kingdom, but we see both kings are involved in this particular passage

00:02:22.160 --> 00:02:23.639
of scripture.

00:02:23.639 --> 00:02:26.559
And by way of introduction, we're going to get through the whole chapter, Lord willing.

00:02:26.559 --> 00:02:30.320
But I want to draw your attention to verse number 18 as we get started.

00:02:30.320 --> 00:02:34.479
Because we've said that it's a longing to see God work and for God to do what only God

00:02:34.479 --> 00:02:38.960
can do, and that our God is able to do exceeding abundantly above all that we ask or think.

00:02:38.960 --> 00:02:43.720
And I've simply titled the message, A Longing to See God Work, part two.

00:02:43.720 --> 00:02:47.360
We did part one last week, part two this evening, part three next week.

00:02:47.360 --> 00:02:52.720
But notice in verse number 18, this is Elisha the prophet speaking in verse number 18.

00:02:52.720 --> 00:02:56.800
And again, we'll catch it all in context as we go through the entirety of this chapter.

00:02:56.800 --> 00:03:03.199
But notice the Bible says this, and this is but a light thing in the sight of the Lord.

00:03:03.199 --> 00:03:06.759
He will deliver the Moabites also into your hand.

00:03:06.759 --> 00:03:11.520
And I want to focus on that phrase to begin verse number 18, where the Bible says, and

00:03:11.520 --> 00:03:15.399
this is but a light thing in the sight of the Lord.

00:03:15.399 --> 00:03:19.240
And we're going to look at that phrase and understand what happens here in this portion

00:03:19.240 --> 00:03:21.080
of Scripture and what God does.

00:03:21.080 --> 00:03:27.000
And we're longing to see God work and understand that God has all power.

00:03:27.000 --> 00:03:31.720
And when God does something miraculous, which he does in this text of Scripture, we find

00:03:31.720 --> 00:03:35.360
that Elisha says, this is but a light thing in the sight of the Lord.

00:03:35.360 --> 00:03:37.919
In other words, it's no problem for God.

00:03:37.919 --> 00:03:40.080
Your problem is no problem for God.

00:03:40.080 --> 00:03:41.080
Amen.

00:03:41.639 --> 00:03:42.839
Do you believe that tonight?

00:03:42.839 --> 00:03:45.559
Sometimes we look at things in our life, we say, but it's such a mountain.

00:03:45.559 --> 00:03:46.559
It's so big.

00:03:46.559 --> 00:03:47.559
And you don't understand.

00:03:47.559 --> 00:03:49.440
No, no, it's no problem for God.

00:03:49.440 --> 00:03:50.440
It's just a light thing.

00:03:50.440 --> 00:03:51.440
It's a small thing.

00:03:51.440 --> 00:03:53.919
It's a, it's no problem whatsoever.

00:03:53.919 --> 00:03:58.600
And we can rejoice in understanding that as we look at the portion of Scripture, and again,

00:03:58.600 --> 00:04:01.199
as we kind of walk our way through it.

00:04:01.199 --> 00:04:05.279
If you're taking notes, I want you to notice first of all, that they strategized.

00:04:05.279 --> 00:04:06.279
They strategized.

00:04:06.479 --> 00:04:11.199
In verses one through eight, we see how the strategy is being developed here.

00:04:11.199 --> 00:04:15.679
Thus I say they strategized and God gives us the setting in the first three verses.

00:04:15.679 --> 00:04:20.519
The Bible says in verse one, now Jehoram, the son of Ahab, began to reign over Israel

00:04:20.519 --> 00:04:26.239
and Samaria in the 18th year of Jehoshaphat, king of Judah, and reigned 12 years.

00:04:26.239 --> 00:04:30.839
And he, Jehoram, wrought evil in the sight of the Lord, but not like his father and like

00:04:30.839 --> 00:04:31.839
his mother.

00:04:31.839 --> 00:04:36.480
His father and mother, that's Ahab and Jezebel, the wicked couple.

00:04:36.480 --> 00:04:40.880
And we find that it says, and not like, but not like his father and like his mother, for

00:04:40.880 --> 00:04:44.279
he put away the image of Baal that his father had made.

00:04:44.279 --> 00:04:49.079
However, we read in verse three, it says, nevertheless, he cleaved under the sins of

00:04:49.079 --> 00:04:51.920
Jeroboam, the son of Nebat, which made Israel to sin.

00:04:51.920 --> 00:04:54.119
He departed not therefrom.

00:04:54.119 --> 00:04:58.600
If you were to go back after the reign of Solomon, there's the divided kingdom, Jeroboam

00:04:58.679 --> 00:05:06.320
to the north, Rehoboam to the south, and Jeroboam instituted some wicked, just various wickedness

00:05:06.320 --> 00:05:12.519
in the northern kingdom with regard to offerings and holy days and all of that sort of thing.

00:05:12.519 --> 00:05:16.959
And we find that often throughout the pages of Scripture with regard to the history of

00:05:16.959 --> 00:05:23.380
Israel at this time, there will be reference back to the sins of Jeroboam.

00:05:23.380 --> 00:05:28.579
And we find that as God gives us the setting here in these first three verses of 2 Kings

00:05:28.579 --> 00:05:31.859
three, that we find that Jehoram is the king of Israel.

00:05:31.859 --> 00:05:33.660
He is the son of Ahab.

00:05:33.660 --> 00:05:36.720
We find that Jehoshaphat is the king of Judah.

00:05:36.720 --> 00:05:42.420
And Jehoshaphat has been reigning for 18 years, according to verse number one, when Jehoram

00:05:42.420 --> 00:05:45.859
becomes the king of Israel at the death of Ahab.

00:05:45.859 --> 00:05:51.320
We'll find as we go through the text of Scripture that Ahab died and there's some rebellion

00:05:51.320 --> 00:05:52.320
that takes place.

00:05:52.320 --> 00:05:57.679
But Elisha is the prophet of God during this particular time.

00:05:57.779 --> 00:06:00.559
The rebellion is recorded for us in verses four and five.

00:06:00.559 --> 00:06:06.760
The Bible says that Misha, king of Moab, was a sheep master and he rendered unto the king

00:06:06.760 --> 00:06:15.079
of Israel, that would be Ahab, and 100,000 lambs and 100,000 rams with the wool.

00:06:15.079 --> 00:06:19.239
Now that's a lot of product that was going into Israel.

00:06:19.239 --> 00:06:24.899
It was almost, if you were to tax of some sort, and we find that because of Ahab and

00:06:24.899 --> 00:06:31.380
because of his reign and the relationship there that the king of Moab, Misha, was sending

00:06:31.380 --> 00:06:32.380
this stuff back.

00:06:32.380 --> 00:06:38.380
And again, it says 100,000 lambs and 100,000 rams with the wool.

00:06:38.380 --> 00:06:43.179
But after Ahab dies and Jehoram becomes the king of Israel, it tells us in verse number

00:06:43.179 --> 00:06:49.779
five, but it came to pass when Ahab was dead that the king of Moab rebelled against the

00:06:49.779 --> 00:06:50.779
king of Israel.

00:06:50.779 --> 00:06:54.299
He decided, I'm not sending that stuff anymore.

00:06:54.299 --> 00:07:01.059
Now this would have a major impact, economical impact, on Israel, and of course, Jehoram's

00:07:01.059 --> 00:07:02.859
not happy about this.

00:07:02.859 --> 00:07:06.260
This would have been something that had been taking place and Jehoram is not happy about

00:07:06.260 --> 00:07:07.660
this rebellion.

00:07:07.660 --> 00:07:12.140
And here's where we really get into where they strategize because we find that what

00:07:12.140 --> 00:07:17.339
happens in verse number six is Jehoram begins to develop this strategy on what is he going

00:07:17.339 --> 00:07:18.339
to do?

00:07:18.339 --> 00:07:22.459
How is he going to respond because of this rebellion of Misha?

00:07:22.459 --> 00:07:27.980
The Bible says in verse six that King Jehoram went out of Samaria the same time, and it

00:07:27.980 --> 00:07:31.500
says this, and numbered all Israel.

00:07:31.500 --> 00:07:36.940
Now oftentimes, as you study again through the portion of history in Israel's history

00:07:36.940 --> 00:07:42.140
with regard to the kings and during that period of time, when the Bible will reference that

00:07:42.140 --> 00:07:46.700
the king went out and numbered his people, there was often a point for that, and that

00:07:46.700 --> 00:07:48.500
was that they were preparing for war.

00:07:48.540 --> 00:07:53.540
It was a situation in which they were understanding that I need to figure out how many people

00:07:53.540 --> 00:07:57.339
I have so that I can determine if I'm ready to go into battle.

00:07:57.339 --> 00:08:02.899
And so the Bible says that he, the king of Israel, Jehoram, that he went out of Samaria

00:08:02.899 --> 00:08:05.739
the same time and numbered all Israel.

00:08:05.739 --> 00:08:10.260
Not only did he number the people of Israel, but according to verse number seven, the Bible

00:08:10.260 --> 00:08:16.779
says that he went and sent to Jehoshaphat, the king of Judah, and here's what he says.

00:08:16.779 --> 00:08:20.739
The king of Moab hath rebelled against me.

00:08:20.739 --> 00:08:24.579
Wilt thou go with me against Moab to battle?

00:08:24.579 --> 00:08:29.700
And he, Jehoshaphat, said to Jehoram, I will go up.

00:08:29.700 --> 00:08:37.400
I am as thou art, my people as thy people, and my horses as thy horses.

00:08:37.400 --> 00:08:42.979
Now understand with me just for a moment, we mentioned a little bit about Jehoram, Jehoshaphat

00:08:43.140 --> 00:08:45.099
as the king of Judah.

00:08:45.099 --> 00:08:50.080
If we were to say broadly speaking, Jehoshaphat's basically a good king.

00:08:50.080 --> 00:08:55.739
There's some good things that happened in Judah during the reign of Jehoshaphat.

00:08:55.739 --> 00:08:58.340
But we find that he made some poor decisions.

00:08:58.340 --> 00:09:00.039
One of them is recorded here.

00:09:00.039 --> 00:09:05.020
We find that he also made affinity with Ahab, the Bible tells us, and that was a poor decision

00:09:05.020 --> 00:09:06.580
on the part of Jehoshaphat.

00:09:06.580 --> 00:09:12.299
But here, as Jehoram comes, and again, we're looking at this strategy and how they strategized

00:09:12.299 --> 00:09:16.659
and Jehoram is not happy about this rebellion of Mesha.

00:09:16.659 --> 00:09:22.099
He wants that product, those goods, to continue to flow in, and the rebellion is going to

00:09:22.099 --> 00:09:23.099
impact him.

00:09:23.099 --> 00:09:26.099
So he numbers his people, and he says, I'm going to need some help.

00:09:26.099 --> 00:09:31.179
And so he goes to Jehoshaphat, and there's really this confederacy or this coalition

00:09:31.179 --> 00:09:34.619
that is being formed, and Jehoshaphat agrees.

00:09:34.619 --> 00:09:39.940
He says, I am as thou art, my people as thy people, and my horses as thy horses.

00:09:40.099 --> 00:09:47.179
So we find that Jehoshaphat agrees to, and they've made this strategy, but the strategy

00:09:47.179 --> 00:09:51.219
continues to be developed, for we find that in verse number eight, there's a question

00:09:51.219 --> 00:09:54.500
asked with regard to which way they would go up.

00:09:54.500 --> 00:09:59.059
How would they enter into, how would they attack Moab?

00:09:59.059 --> 00:10:00.059
So we find that in verse number eight.

00:10:00.059 --> 00:10:02.439
he said, which way shall we go up?

00:10:02.439 --> 00:10:06.239
And he answered, the way through the wilderness of Edom.

00:10:06.239 --> 00:10:07.759
As we study through the passage,

00:10:07.759 --> 00:10:11.079
we'll find that not only Jehoram, king of Israel,

00:10:11.079 --> 00:10:13.639
Jehoshaphat, the king of Judah,

00:10:13.639 --> 00:10:15.719
but we find that the king of Edom

00:10:15.719 --> 00:10:17.799
is gonna join in with this coalition

00:10:17.799 --> 00:10:19.719
and it's gonna be these three kings

00:10:19.719 --> 00:10:21.919
that are gonna go up against Moab.

00:10:21.919 --> 00:10:25.639
And when Jehoshaphat asks the question in verse number eight,

00:10:25.639 --> 00:10:29.319
we find that Jehoram answers the question and says,

00:10:29.339 --> 00:10:33.019
the way through the wilderness of Edom.

00:10:33.019 --> 00:10:34.779
And so if you were to consider,

00:10:34.779 --> 00:10:36.459
and I don't have a map to show you in here,

00:10:36.459 --> 00:10:39.379
but if you were to consider the geography of Israel,

00:10:39.379 --> 00:10:42.039
you would find if you were to think about the Dead Sea

00:10:42.039 --> 00:10:45.339
being on the eastern part of the land of Israel,

00:10:45.339 --> 00:10:49.619
you would find that Moab would be just east of the Dead Sea

00:10:49.619 --> 00:10:52.259
and Edom would be south of that.

00:10:52.259 --> 00:10:54.099
And so they're gonna go south

00:10:54.099 --> 00:10:55.779
and then they're gonna make this,

00:10:55.799 --> 00:10:57.919
they're gonna go east and then back up north

00:10:57.919 --> 00:10:59.799
to attack Moab.

00:10:59.799 --> 00:11:03.039
And so we think about the way that they strategized

00:11:03.039 --> 00:11:06.119
and when I look at these first eight verses,

00:11:07.159 --> 00:11:10.360
I notice something really important that's missing.

00:11:10.360 --> 00:11:11.519
No one sought God.

00:11:13.159 --> 00:11:14.799
No one sought God.

00:11:14.799 --> 00:11:17.220
I'm gonna count my people and see how many I have.

00:11:17.220 --> 00:11:20.199
I'm gonna contact the king of Judah

00:11:20.199 --> 00:11:22.059
to come and to be with me

00:11:22.059 --> 00:11:26.519
and we're gonna take this direction,

00:11:26.519 --> 00:11:28.040
this is the route that we're gonna go

00:11:28.040 --> 00:11:32.000
in making our attack and they've strategized.

00:11:32.000 --> 00:11:34.040
And sometimes if we're not careful,

00:11:34.040 --> 00:11:36.759
we're talking about a longing to see God work,

00:11:36.759 --> 00:11:40.159
sometimes we don't see God work because we never seek God.

00:11:41.059 --> 00:11:42.239
We just try to figure it out ourselves.

00:11:42.239 --> 00:11:43.720
We strategize.

00:11:43.720 --> 00:11:46.879
We plan, we scheme, we're gonna devise a plan.

00:11:46.879 --> 00:11:50.319
I mean, we've lived life for as long as we've lived life,

00:11:50.319 --> 00:11:51.759
we've done the things that we've done

00:11:52.459 --> 00:11:54.419
and we're gonna come up with a strategy, a plan.

00:11:54.419 --> 00:11:56.720
I need you to do this and I need you to do this

00:11:56.720 --> 00:12:01.059
and I said this before, but oftentimes what happens

00:12:01.059 --> 00:12:03.099
and it's a danger that we face

00:12:03.099 --> 00:12:06.059
is sometimes we develop all of our plans

00:12:06.059 --> 00:12:07.899
and we get done developing all of our plans.

00:12:07.899 --> 00:12:10.419
We get done the strategy session, if you will,

00:12:10.419 --> 00:12:12.300
and then we say, okay, now God,

00:12:12.300 --> 00:12:15.039
we're gonna pray that you bless our plans.

00:12:16.979 --> 00:12:18.979
But you know how God wants us to do it?

00:12:18.979 --> 00:12:23.599
He wants us to seek him and find out what his plan is

00:12:23.599 --> 00:12:27.000
and then we do what his plan is

00:12:27.000 --> 00:12:29.880
and we find that they strategized

00:12:29.880 --> 00:12:31.800
and they had everything.

00:12:31.800 --> 00:12:33.599
I mean, I think from a human perspective,

00:12:33.599 --> 00:12:35.800
from a military perspective,

00:12:35.800 --> 00:12:38.559
if they were to look at the battle plan, if you will,

00:12:38.559 --> 00:12:40.160
on what they were gonna do, why?

00:12:40.160 --> 00:12:43.959
Because we really want those goods to flow back into Israel.

00:12:43.959 --> 00:12:46.000
That was the perspective of Jehoram

00:12:46.000 --> 00:12:47.639
and so we're gonna do it by force

00:12:47.639 --> 00:12:49.699
and we have the people,

00:12:49.699 --> 00:12:52.660
we have the path that we're gonna go

00:12:52.660 --> 00:12:55.300
and everything, I mean, we have this plan.

00:12:56.619 --> 00:12:59.539
But we find that they strategized

00:12:59.539 --> 00:13:02.020
and as we continue to move through the text of scripture,

00:13:02.020 --> 00:13:05.220
I'm gonna say this, number two, they sought the Lord.

00:13:05.220 --> 00:13:07.339
But I want you to see that they sought the Lord

00:13:07.339 --> 00:13:10.339
only because of Jehoshaphat

00:13:11.380 --> 00:13:13.619
and only because they encountered a problem.

00:13:15.139 --> 00:13:16.539
There's a lessons for us to learn

00:13:16.539 --> 00:13:18.319
through this text of scripture.

00:13:18.319 --> 00:13:20.199
Sometimes what happens is we strategize

00:13:20.199 --> 00:13:22.839
just like Jehoram did and then something doesn't work out,

00:13:22.839 --> 00:13:25.739
we're like, oh, maybe we should seek God.

00:13:25.739 --> 00:13:28.720
But seeking God should be our first response,

00:13:28.720 --> 00:13:30.919
not after we encounter a problem

00:13:30.919 --> 00:13:33.080
trying to do it our own way.

00:13:33.080 --> 00:13:35.720
And we find that as we come to verse number nine

00:13:35.720 --> 00:13:36.679
of the text of scripture

00:13:36.679 --> 00:13:38.599
and really verses nine through 14, number two,

00:13:38.599 --> 00:13:40.080
they sought the Lord.

00:13:40.080 --> 00:13:41.880
Notice what the Bible says in verse nine.

00:13:41.880 --> 00:13:45.660
So the king of Israel went and the king of Judah

00:13:45.660 --> 00:13:46.839
and the king of Edom, again,

00:13:46.839 --> 00:13:49.599
this coalition that had been formed.

00:13:49.599 --> 00:13:51.679
And it says, and they fetched a compass

00:13:51.679 --> 00:13:54.160
of seven days journey.

00:13:54.160 --> 00:13:56.239
Notice what the Bible says.

00:13:56.239 --> 00:13:59.959
There was no water for the host

00:13:59.959 --> 00:14:03.319
and for the cattle that followed them.

00:14:03.319 --> 00:14:05.099
Now, no water is a problem.

00:14:06.639 --> 00:14:08.539
If you know about that part of Israel,

00:14:08.539 --> 00:14:11.160
I mean, a lot of Israel is this way,

00:14:11.160 --> 00:14:15.699
but I mean, it's dry, it's hot.

00:14:15.699 --> 00:14:18.940
I remember being there and climbing up Masada

00:14:18.940 --> 00:14:20.459
would be in that same region

00:14:20.459 --> 00:14:22.019
of where they're kind of located.

00:14:22.019 --> 00:14:23.179
And I remember climbing up Masada

00:14:23.179 --> 00:14:27.660
